parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power sliding doors can cause the doors to open or close unexpectedly, leading to accidents or injuries, especially when the vehicle is in motion.
symptoms: Doors open or close unexpectedly
doors stick or fail to close
doors bounce back open
alarms sound
and locks malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the tire can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: Tire blowout
loss of control
and vehicle damage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS system can cause accidents, injuries, and loss of control.
symptoms: ABS light comes on
brakes pulse
and difficulty stopping the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning sliding doors can cause inconvenience, safety risks, and even accidents, especially when they open or close unexpectedly while driving.
symptoms: The doors may open or close randomly
stick
or refuse to open/close
accompanied by a dinging noise or alarm.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The electrical system failures can lead to loss of critical functions, such as lighting, wipers, and blower fans, which can compromise safety while driving.
symptoms: The failures may manifest as flashing dashboard lights
stalling
or complete loss of electrical power
accompanied by smoke or fire in some cases.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The battery and alternator problems can cause unexpected stalling, loss of power, and even fires, which can lead to accidents or strand the driver.
symptoms: The issues may cause the battery to fail without warning
with green or white deposits on the terminals
or excessive voltage output from the alternator.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Reduced Engine Power and Check Engine Light
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The reduced engine power and check engine light can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, or strand the driver, especially if the issue occurs while driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The issues may manifest as a sudden loss of power
accompanied by the check engine light and reduced engine performance.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The headlight and taillight failures can cause reduced visibility, accidents, or strand the driver, especially at night or in low-light conditions.
symptoms: The issues may cause the headlights or taillights to fail suddenly
without warning
or intermittently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the steering wheel to seize or lock up, making it difficult or impossible to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The steering wheel feels loose or has a floating sensation
the steering wheel makes a clicking or clunking sound
the steering wheel seizes or locks up
the vehicle is difficult to steer
the vehicle makes a wooing or scrubbing noise
the power steering fluid level is low.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering intermediate shaft can cause the steering wheel to feel loose or have a floating sensation, making it difficult to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The steering wheel feels loose or has a floating sensation
the steering wheel makes a clunking sound
the vehicle is difficult to steer
the intermediate shaft is faulty.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering column can cause the steering wheel to seize or lock up, making it difficult or impossible to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The steering wheel feels loose or has a floating sensation
the steering wheel makes a clicking or clunking sound
the steering wheel seizes or locks up
the vehicle is difficult to steer.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power or stall, making it difficult or impossible to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The vehicle loses power or stalls
the transmission makes a strange noise
the vehicle is difficult to shift gears.
